TITLE.0: Ulysses/SWICS Full Resolution Matrix Rate Data

Project.0: NSSDC>National Space Science Data Center Archived Data

Generated_by.0: Physics Institute, University of Bern, Bern, Switzerland

TEXT.0: The Ulysses/SWICS instrument is a mass spectrometer combining an

TEXT.1: electrostatic analyzer with post acceleration, followed by a time-of-flight

TEXT.2: and energy measurement. The instrument covers an energy per charge range

TEXT.3: from 0.16 to 59.6 keV/e with a time resolution of about 13 minutes.

TEXT.4: SWICS is designed to determine uniquely the elemental and ionic-charge

TEXT.5: composition, the temperatures and mean speeds of all major solar wind ions,

TEXT.6: from H through Fe. For more information see G. Gloeckler, J. Geiss et al.,

TEXT.8: This archive consists of all 18 Matrix Rates (MR) as a function of energy

TEXT.9: per charge (E/q) and of time. Each MR represents a specific element in one

TEXT.10: or several ionization states, but it may also contain significant

TEXT.11: contributions from neighbouring elements due to spillover. The MRs are given

TEXT.12: in units of count rates only. The accompanying SAPRO (SWICS Archive

TEXT.13: Processor) software can be used both to convert the MR count rates to

TEXT.14: physical units (differential flux, phase space density), to correct for

TEXT.15: spillover between different MRs, and to obtain kinetic parameters (density,

TEXT.16: speed, thermal speed) of selected ions (to be used with caution).
